{
  "texts": [
    "For A2C, displayed in Fig. 8b, using replay buffers with data samples from previous episodes, except for Top current, gives slightly lower episodic reward compared to using only data sampled in the current episode.",
    "All replay buffers only using immediate samples give an average episodic reward close to 1.",
    "One should note that the short drop of reward for All current occurs due to the resetting of the parameters of one run to that of the pretrained model, since the policy samples less than 80% valid molecules for more than 10 consecutive episodes.",
    "After restarting, it quickly gets back on track.",
    "This run is kept to highlight that it is possible for the networks to diverge from the pre-trained model and forget how to generate valid SMILES strings."
  ]
}